  <span id="freeText11117700145210845959" style="display:none">*** Copy given in exchange for a review from Goodreads Group Read it &amp; Reap***<br /><br />I have never read a short story like this, but then I am hardly a short story connoisseur. I have read some that have been dramatic and impactful and some that have been week and lifeless. I am not exactly sure where this story falls. I like reading stories set in other countries, especially India. I find India endlessly fascinating. To me, I find the culture a beatifically heartbreaking microcosm of mankind’s strengths and weaknesses. India is such a land of wealth and poverty in more that just the literal sense. <br /> <br />I guess this story was a brief snapshot of this theme. A tale of a man’s loyalty and desire to honor family above all while simultaneously debasing and denying those very values.<br />A subtle tail of how one person’s actions or in fact, inactions, can impact a great many lives. <br /><br />I was surprised at how many layers the author was able to put into so short a tail. I kept going back to reread pages after each revelation and I think I will reread the entire thing at some point. <br /></span>
