<div id="review_1221257657" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1221257657" />
    <a title="Jennifer MacDonald" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1122006-jennifer-macdonald"><img alt="Jennifer MacDonald" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1221257657?book_show_action=true">Mar 07, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jennifer MacDonald" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jennifer MacDonald" href="/user/show/1122006-jennifer-macdonald">Jennifer MacDonald</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1221257657" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6349733023083076453">I like a book that wraps up a story, unless there is a sequel, in which case, most of the story should be tidied up and a little bit left for the next book. This short story left everything hanging. Which I think for the disjointed way it was put together and since the main POV is from a dying old man, it actually is appropriate. I guess what I&apos;m saying is that the story is written in a realistic style. Old memories and regrets, never ending family quarrels and secrets. Life is messy and doesn&apos;t</span>
  <span id="freeText6349733023083076453" style="display:none">I like a book that wraps up a story, unless there is a sequel, in which case, most of the story should be tidied up and a little bit left for the next book. This short story left everything hanging. Which I think for the disjointed way it was put together and since the main POV is from a dying old man, it actually is appropriate. I guess what I'm saying is that the story is written in a realistic style. Old memories and regrets, never ending family quarrels and secrets. Life is messy and doesn't have a tidy ending.</span>
  <a data-text-id="6349733023083076453" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


